<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEXICAN stocks ended a six-session winning streak and closed lower as
investors grew cautious in late trade ahead of the US House of
Representatives' Nafta vote. The IPC index was off 10.85 at 2,148.50 after
an intraday record high of 2,177.30. Volume was a brisk 170.8m shares.
