<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / World Commodities Prices: WooL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There were some signs this week that the wool market recovery might have
spent itself, if only for the time being. In Australia the market indicator
after rising to 511 cents a kg. fell back to 503 yesterday, and clearances
at two of the three selling centres, Fremantle and Sydney, were less than
90%. softness in the Australian dollar has also had a slight cheapening
effect for buyers in many countries. A setback after almost three months of
rising prices and an advance of 25% overall is not causing great concern in
the trade.
