fourth-quarter earnings would also exceed a year earlier.
Maple Leaf said the cost-cutting and rationalisation in its feed, poultry
and rendering operations have paid off in sharply higher earnings.
But earnings from processed foods were hit by higher raw material costs and
a move by consumers to cheaper products.
The company said it aims to improve performance by launching new products
and cutting costs, giving greater attention to private labels, and by
further inroads into the US market.
