FT  18 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Water companies make progress
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two water companies controlled by Lyonnaise des Dumez returned higher
profits for the half year ended September 30.
Suffolk Water's rose from Pounds 2.4m to Pounds 2.9m pre-tax on turnover of
Pounds 9.9m (Pounds 8.2m). Earnings per share emerged at 56p (43p) but the
interim dividend is 23.3p (23.7p).
Essex Water returned pre-tax profits of Pounds 9.9m against Pounds 9.4m on
turnover of Pounds 35.4m (Pounds 33m).
Earnings per share were 90p (113p). The interim dividend on the voting A
shares and non-voting B shares is 39.1p (36.8p).
