<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / Cambridgeshire County Council votes to ban cycles from two
pedestrian streets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cambridgeshire County Council has voted to ban cyclists from two central
pedestrian streets in Cambridge.
Cycle City, as it is known to CB enthusiasts, will no longer welcome
bicycles between 10am and 4pm, on Sydney Street, a shopping thoroughfare,
and Market Street (above). A survey showed that while 2,800 pedestrians used
Sydney Street per hour, so did 430 cyclists.
The ban, designed to improve safety and enhance the environment for
shoppers, has split public opinion, both between town and gown and between
the main parties.
The Labour-controlled city council is against the ban, while the Labour
group on county council supported the Tories, who introduced an experimental
ban in the summer of 1991.
</TEXT>
