<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / National print deals to resume
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL PAY bargaining is to resume in the printing industry in 1994 after
a year's suspension, it was announced yesterday by the printing employers'
federation and the GPMU print union.
The decision follows intensive negotiations between the two sides and
widespread consultation among printing companies. It represents a climbdown
by the employers federation, which made clear earlier this year that it
wanted to scrap the national wage agreement in favour of company deals. But
the federation found its affiliate members were almost evenly divided in
their views on whether to return to national pay bargaining. While larger
printing companies saw the value of dealing with pay themselves, medium and
smaller-sized companies preferred the stability ensured by a centralised
agreement.
</TEXT>
