<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / Shake-up of professions urged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S professions should be scrutinised for restrictive practices by the
Office of Fair Trading, according to Mr Graham Mather, president of the
European Policy Forum, the cross-party think-tank.
Mr Mather yesterday told the Royal Institute of British Architects that
professions such as doctors and lawyers had escaped the reforming zeal of
Thatcherism. They lagged behind other businesses, the utilities and
public-sector organisations in the quality of service they gave to their
customers, he said.
'Many professions have failed to stamp out wildly misleading underestimates
of likely charges, dilatory approaches to work, and a detachment from their
customers' priorities, timetables and commercial constraints,' he added.
Their restrictive practices should be reviewed and dealt with, he said.
</TEXT>
