action at Ellesmere Port is starting with shop steward approval because of
what the union calls 'unavoidable delays in collecting the information
required by the ballot scrutineers' in the rest of the company which
prevented co-ordination of the voting across the Vauxhall plants.
Officials of other unions believe the majority of manual workers will accept
the pay offer, which is in line with the rises agreed at Ford last week
which appear to be winning rank-and-file support.
